  "response": "Yes, many countries have specific anti-money laundering (AML) laws. In the United States, key laws include the Bank Secrecy Act and the USA PATRIOT Act. These laws require financial institutions to report suspicious transactions, conduct customer due diligence, and maintain records to help prevent money laundering. Similar laws exist in many other countries, with international organizations like the Financial Action Task Force (FATF) setting global standards for combating money laundering.",
